Slovakia’s SaS Party Says It Won’t Change Its Position on EFSF

-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 
2011-10-10T13:21:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/slovakia-s-sas-party-says-it-won-t-change-its-position-on-efsf.html
Slovakia’s Freedom and Solidarity
Party, a junior coalition member better known as SaS, will not
change its stance on the European Union’s current bailout fund,
said party leader Richard Sulik in Bratislava today.  Sulik said the party won’t take responsibility for a
collapse of the government if happens because of the vote.  To contact the reporter on this story:
